3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates AVAX/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium index. The funding rate is capped at ±2.5% per interval to prevent extreme payments. When AVAX perpetual trades above spot prices, long positions pay shorts, creating potential arbitrage opportunities for delta-neutral strategies. Bitget's maker-taker fee structure of 0.02%/0.06% applies to all funding rate positions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AVAX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX represents Avalanche's native token with significant DeFi and subnet activity driving volatility and funding rate premiums. The token's large trading volume on Bitget ensures tight spreads and sufficient liquidity for executing multi-leg arbitrage strategies without significant slippage."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical AVAX Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AVAX/USDT funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during subnet launches or major ecosystem announcements. During the 2024 subnet expansion phase, funding rates peaked at +0.8% as retail traders heavily favored long positions. Bear market periods show more balanced or negative funding rates as short interest increases. The token's correlation with broader L1 sentiment creates predictable funding rate cycles around major Avalanche protocol updates."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Delta-neutral arbitrage works best when AVAX funding rates exceed 0.15% per interval, covering transaction costs and providing meaningful returns. Traders can short AVAX perpetuals on Bitget while buying spot AVAX on exchanges like Coinbase or Binance to hedge price exposure. Bitget's copy trading feature allows following experienced funding rate arbitrageurs, though this may increase competition for profitable opportunities. The exchange's fast listing of AVAX-related tokens provides additional cross-pair arbitrage possibilities during high volatility periods."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Funding rate arbitrage on Bitget carries risks including basis convergence during low volatility periods and potential liquidation if hedged positions diverge significantly. AVAX's price volatility can create temporary unrealized losses in delta-neutral strategies if rebalancing is delayed. Bitget's newer market presence means lower institutional participation compared to established exchanges, potentially creating more retail-driven funding rate volatility. Weekend funding rates often show different patterns due to reduced institutional activity, requiring adjusted position sizing and risk management protocols."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical AVAX funding rates on Bitget compared to other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget AVAX funding rates average 0.05-0.15% per 8-hour period, often 10-20 basis points higher than Binance due to retail trader preference for long positions. This premium creates consistent arbitrage opportunities for sophisticated traders."},{"question":"How does Bitget's copy trading affect AVAX funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"Copy trading can reduce funding rate premiums as more traders replicate successful arbitrage strategies. However, it also provides liquidity and can create temporary dislocations when copied strategies exit simultaneously during market stress."},{"question":"What position sizes work best for AVAX funding arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"Optimal position sizes range from $10,000 to $100,000 equivalent, balancing sufficient returns against liquidity constraints. Larger positions may face slippage during volatile periods when AVAX experiences rapid price movements."},{"question":"How do Bitget's margin requirements affect AVAX arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Bitget requires 10% initial margin for AVAX perpetuals with 10x maximum leverage. Cross-margin mode allows using other collateral, enabling more efficient capital utilization for multi-pair arbitrage strategies including AVAX hedging."}]}]
